  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this long-term study is to investigate the effect of roflumilast (APTA-2217) on
      the long-term safety in patients with asthma, who completed the 24-week evaluation of study
      APTA-2217-05. Roflumilast will be administered orally once daily. The present study consists
      of a 28 weeks treatment period, and is the extension of the 24-week study APTA-2217-05
      (registered study). The study will provide further long-term safety and efficacy data of
      roflumilast.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
